results.description: My first time ever seeing these rare nearly all white deer in the wild.  I spotted this one just before sunrise in the Pine Barrens in the middle of southern New Jersey.  When I first caught a glimpse of it I thought it was trash on the far side of a lake.  When I pointed the lens at it I quickly realized it was a piebald whitetail deer and a great looking one at that.  The calm morning gave a nice reflection on the water.  I watched this deer for maybe 2 minutes before it disappeared into the forest.
